parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Airbag Occupancy Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger airbag occupancy sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on and off intermittently
the passenger airbag "off" indicator lights up
the airbag warning lamp is activated
the passenger airbag may not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag control unit can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, potentially leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on and off intermittently
the airbag warning lamp is activated
the airbag may not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles with safety defects on the road, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealers are unable to obtain parts for recall repairs
owners are unable to have recalls repaired
owners are left with safety hazards in their vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Long Brake Pedal Travel and Spongy Brakes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake pedal travel and spongy brake feel can cause delayed or inadequate braking, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in low-speed situations like parking or approaching stop signs.
symptoms: Long brake pedal travel
spongy brake feel
brakes engage abruptly after initial delay
need to pump brakes to achieve desired braking
difficulty stopping in time
especially in low-speed situations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can lead to accidents, especially on high-speed roads or in tight spaces, as the driver may struggle to maintain control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power steering
difficulty steering
steering feels heavy or manual
intermittent power steering failure
vehicle veers in direction of steer
warning lights or messages on the dashboard (e.g.
"Power Steering Malfunction").

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's transmission fault can cause the vehicle to jerk or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into jerking mode while driving without warning
the safety light comes on as transmission fault
the vehicle loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leaks from Timing Case and Valve Cover Gasket
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to loss of engine performance.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the timing case over bolts
oil leaking from the valve cover gasket onto the side of the engine
slight wetness visible at the valve cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Control Fault and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine control fault can cause the vehicle to lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power while driving
the "Engine Control Fault" indicator illuminates
the vehicle operates normally after restarting the engine.
